OL,6,
OL,7,F The final live news programme
OL,8,Fproduced specifically for the BBC News
OL,9,FChannel will air at 5pm on Friday 3rd
OL,10,FMarch.
OL,11,F Top-of-the-hour opening headlines
OL,12,Fwill be dropped. Live news programmes
OL,13,Fwill start with opening titles and will
OL,14,Fimmediately link into the lead story.
OL,15,F Commercial breaks on the
OL,16,Finternational version of the channel
OL,17,Fwill be filled with UK-focussed content
OL,18,Fin the UK.
OL,19,F Some sport bulletins will be for a UK
OL,20,Faudience only, others will be broadcast
OL,21,Fto both a UK and international
OL,22,Faudience.
OL,23,F Between 9am and 7pm, live news will
OL,24,Fbe based in Studio E. Evenings and
OL,25,Fovernight will come from Studio C. From
OL,3,CBBC News Channel to merge with
OL,4,Cinternational channel on 6th March?
